<h1>Levenshtein in Ruby 1.9</h1>
<p>In Ruby 1.8, I would use the gem &#39;levenshtein&#39;... well that doesn&#39;t work
in 1.9. So you need to install the gem &#39;text&#39;.</p>
<p>Then the call is as simple as:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-ruby">Text::Levenshtein.distance(&#39;hello&#39;, &#39;hell&#39;)</code></pre>
